annotations.title: HalfStack Hexes
annotations.description:
This is a collection of hexagonal stickers I've acquired after attending the last few HalfStacks in London.

The latest acquisitions are the orange HalfStack London sticker featuring the cassette and the blue hex sticker featuring the London Eye and the Elizabeth Tower (fun fact: Big Ben is the name of the bell!), which I picked up at HalfStack London in November 2024.

annotations.title: Fat Nuggets
annotations.description: Fat Nuggets is a pig in the television series Hazbin Hotel, owned by one of the characters. I won't give any spoilers here, but I can highly recommend watching Hazbin Hotel and its spin-off series, Helluva Boss. This sticker was given to me by a friend while she lived in Portsmouth.

annotations.title: Monzo Rocket
annotations.description: This is a sticker I've acquired during my time at Monzo. Monzo loves their stickers, and their emoji!

annotations.title: uncodebar Square
annotations.description: This one I most likely picked up at uncodebar in 2022, although I'm not 100% sure. It's definitely a fun unconference I make the effort to go to every year. There are always incredibly talented speakers, and I always bump into one or two people I haven't seen in a while.

annotations.title: Bigfoot
annotations.description: This fuzzy Bigfoot sticker was given to me by a friend! It's Bigfoot, from the Anti Crypto Cryptid Club, created by the crypto researcher Molly White.

annotations.title: codebar Square
annotations.description: Another codebar sticker! I can't remember where I picked this one up.

annotations.title: Glittery codebar
annotations.description: I've volunteered with codebar since my first uncodebar in October 2022. I've given conference talks, hosted panel discussions and travelled around Europe for their events. I love the organisation, what it does and what it represents, and you can tell by all the stickers on my laptop  and especially by this extra glittery one!

annotations.title: Monzo Hackathon 2024
annotations.description: Obtained at the internal Monzo Hackathon 2024! Built some cool stuff that'll hopefully be shipped to customers in the first calendar half of 2025, so keep your eyes peeled!

I obtained this sticker through extensive sticker trading at Electromagnetic Field 2024.

This was one of the stickers I liked the most (and I identify with it the most because, c'mon, I have no clue what I'm doing even on the best of days), and so on it got stuck!

annotations.title: codebar Festival
annotations.description: I obtained this at codebar Festival in September 2023, where I presented a panel discussion about the importance of diversity in technology. Fun fact: it was my first panel discussion, and I managed to wrangle all the speakers and pull it off flawlessly!

annotations.title: Property of Aperture Laboratories
annotations.description: A sticker obtained at Electromagnetic Field 2024 through some skilful sticker trading.

annotations.title: I helped!
annotations.description: I got this sticker by volunteering to help with the phones at Electromagnetic Field 2024! Their phone system is bogglingly complex, and maintained by skilful, dedicated and hardworking volunteers. It's a shame the stickers weren't hexagonal, as some of the enamel pins available are.

annotations.title: Electromagnetic Field 2024
annotations.description: Obtained at Electromagnetic Field 2024. I believe this came with their Tildagon electronic badge, although I may have picked it up randomly.

annotations.title: Pertty Good!
annotations.description: Given to me by a lovely bloke on the dance floor at Electromagnetic Field 2024. Stuck to my t-shirt, and later transferred to my laptop.
